title: Current Spill - 20 May 2010, 2253
name: Current Spill - 20 May 2010, 2253
description:
Extent of Deepwater Horizon surface oil spill, as of May 20, 2010.  Based on NOAA/NESDIS satellite imagery, as provided by Louisiana GOHSEP.

Confidence is high for most portions of this image. In some of the areas south of Louisiana, near 28 30'N 88 30'W, it was difficult to determine where the southernmost boundary was due to the nature of the slick in this area. The image cuts off at 87 15'W not allowing possible oil east of there to be seen. based on the is image we are assuming that there is oil in the area of 20 - 29 30'N east of 87 15'W.
